Description: A comprehensive toolkit for analyzing and optimizing PTSD 
    (Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder) diagnostic criteria using PCL-5 (PTSD 
    Checklist for DSM-5) data. The package provides functions to identify 
    optimal subsets of PCL-5 items that maintain diagnostic accuracy while 
    reducing assessment burden. It includes tools for both hierarchical 
    (cluster-based) and non-hierarchical symptom combinations, calculation of 
    diagnostic metrics, and comparison with standard DSM-5 criteria. Model
    validation is conducted using holdout and cross-validation methods to
    assess robustness and generalizability of the results.
